sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant SIG as Signal / Exception
    participant PY  as Python Gateway
    participant C   as C Binary
    participant MB  as Modbus Device

    Note over SIG,PY: teardown on one of three paths

    alt C Process
        C  -->> PY: stdout closed
    else SIGINT
        SIG ->> PY: interrupt / signal
    else Exception
        PY  ->> PY: exception propagates
    end

    Note over PY,C: EpriClient.__exit__() → stop()

    PY  ->>  C: SIGTERM
    PY  ->>  PY: wait(timeout = 5s)

    alt 5s graceful exit
        C  -->> PY: process terminated
    else timeout exceeded
        PY  ->>  C: SIGKILL (force kill)
        C  -->> PY: killed
    end

    Note over PY,MB: FieldProtocol.__exit__() → disconnect()

    PY  ->>  MB: close TCP connection
    MB -->>  PY: disconnected

    Note over PY: process exits
    Note over MB: ⚠ if an event was active when teardown began,<br/>last-written register values remain on the device.<br/>Registers are NOT automatically relinquished on crash.
